Timoshenko had been sentenced to seven years in prison in October for concluding an alleged adverse agreement with Russia on the purchase of natural gas.
The judgment is not yet valid; in December the appeal of the convicted shall be negotiated before the Court.
Timoshenko himself describes the judgment as the political revenge of the regime, and also in the West the trial raised the suspicion of the bias of the court.
The request to remove point 365, on the basis of which the Prime Minister was condemned, from the Criminal Code, was supported by 147 Members.
226 votes would have been necessary for its adoption.
