As long as you think people have come because of music, remember that you have to pay attention to the music and to what she has created, without losing your mind to being a famous rock star. We have never been interested in that anyway.
What are your memories of your other Mother Love Bone project?
I think we wrote very good songs and at the beginning it was great.
For three years we were a band that had never released a record until the death of Andy (Andrew Woods).
We were disappointed to have needed so long. We are still good with Bruce (Fairweather) and Greg (Gilmore) who built up the band with us. When I hear a song or see photos, I think about what an incredible person Andy was and how he made me laugh. It was always a pleasure to go to work, to laugh together and talk about music and football and many other topics.
He was an extraordinary person and we miss him.
The local band Las Robertas is responsible for the opening of the show in Costa Rica.
